second series that I wrote.

00:05:45.110 --> 00:05:46.670
And I wrote those for
Simon and Schuster.

00:05:46.670 --> 00:05:50.790
And it was just such a
wonderful opportunity to be able

00:05:50.790 --> 00:05:52.630
to do both fiction
and nonfiction.

00:05:52.630 --> 00:05:54.550
And I did that for
the longest time.

00:05:54.550 --> 00:05:58.220
So, when National
Geographic came along,

00:05:58.220 --> 00:06:01.500
it was the perfect
opportunity to take what I knew

00:06:01.500 --> 00:06:04.430
about writing nonfiction and
when I knew about fiction

00:06:04.430 --> 00:06:05.900
and put them together.

00:06:05.900 --> 00:06:08.280
So, let me tell you a little
bit about Explorer Academy.

00:06:08.280 --> 00:06:11.840
Explorer Academy is the story
of 12 year old Cruz Coronado.

00:06:11.840 --> 00:06:17.020
And he has been accepted into
a very elite school for tours.

00:06:17.020 --> 00:06:19.700
And he's going to
travel around the world,

00:06:19.700 --> 00:06:23.150
learning about all different
kinds of issues and things

00:06:23.150 --> 00:06:24.490
that are going on in the world.

00:06:24.490 --> 00:06:28.370
He's going to travel to faraway
places and talk to animals

00:06:28.370 --> 00:06:31.170
and get involved in
preserving the earth.

00:06:31.170 --> 00:06:34.430
And he's going to do it
with 23 very good friends.

00:06:34.430 --> 00:06:37.080
And along the way,
Cruz has a mystery

00:06:37.080 --> 00:06:38.510
that he's going to solve.

00:06:38.510 --> 00:06:41.110
And you, as the reader, are
going to help him solve it.

00:06:41.110 --> 00:06:44.060
Because you get to
crack the clues

00:06:44.060 --> 00:06:47.050
and the puzzles along with Cruz.

