00:07:11.560 --> 00:07:13.950
Alright, so what inspired
me to write this series?

00:07:13.950 --> 00:07:15.930
Well, really it was
the explorers

00:07:15.930 --> 00:07:17.640
of National Geographic.

00:07:17.640 --> 00:07:21.070
All the archeologists
and the marine biologists

00:07:21.070 --> 00:07:25.840
and the scientists of National
Geographic inspired me.

00:07:25.840 --> 00:07:30.010
Now in the book, Cruz
and his friends get

00:07:30.010 --> 00:07:31.460
to do augmented reality.

00:07:31.460 --> 00:07:32.760
So, you know what that is?

00:07:32.760 --> 00:07:34.470
That's like virtual reality.

00:07:34.470 --> 00:07:36.850
They get to go to what's
called a computer animated

00:07:36.850 --> 00:07:38.650
virtual experience.

00:07:38.650 --> 00:07:40.670
And they get to explore things

00:07:40.670 --> 00:07:42.710
without really ever
leaving home.

00:07:42.710 --> 00:07:45.420
And that's how they
learn how to train.

00:07:45.420 --> 00:07:48.710
And so, I had to create
some interesting things

00:07:48.710 --> 00:07:50.530
for Explorer Academy.

00:07:50.530 --> 00:07:53.690
And one of those things that I
thought would be fun would be--

00:07:53.690 --> 00:07:56.570
because I wore glasses
as a kid and I still do--

00:07:56.570 --> 00:08:00.630
glasses that change color
and shape with your emotion.

00:08:00.630 --> 00:08:02.470
So, I see a few kids
here wearing glasses.

00:08:02.470 --> 00:08:05.860
Can you imagine what it would
be like if you were angry

00:08:05.860 --> 00:08:10.150
and your glasses got red and
started, you know, spewing fire?

00:08:10.150 --> 00:08:11.650
And I thought this would
be really fun to do.

00:08:11.650 --> 00:08:14.990
And what I found out
is that explorers

00:08:14.990 --> 00:08:18.230
at National Geographic are
already doing something very

00:08:18.230 --> 00:08:19.530
similar to that.

00:08:19.530 --> 00:08:22.940
There are scientists that are
already working on materials

00:08:22.940 --> 00:08:26.400
that can actually change color
and shape and texture based

00:08:26.400 --> 00:08:29.460
on your environment and
based on h ow you feel.

00:08:29.460 --> 00:08:32.060
And say if it's raining outside,
you could actually have a coat

00:08:32.060 --> 00:08:34.360
that automatically
opens on its own.

00:08:34.360 --> 00:08:38.550
So, I found some pretty amazing
technology is already happening

00:08:38.550 --> 00:08:39.850
right now.

00:08:39.850 --> 00:08:41.490
It's not even science fiction.

00:08:41.490 --> 00:08:45.710
So, Cruz has a honeybee
drone, and her name is Mel.

00:08:45.710 --> 00:08:47.620
And she goes with
him everywhere.

00:08:47.620 --> 00:08:49.480
And again, I thought,
well, you know,

00:08:49.480 --> 00:08:51.590
there's still a little
bit science fiction.

00:08:51.590 --> 00:08:54.730
But in actuality, scientists
are already doing this.

00:08:54.730 --> 00:08:57.450
They are already developing--
you see on the left-hand side--

00:08:57.450 --> 00:08:59.810
there already developing
tiny drones.

00:08:59.810 --> 00:09:04.180
And these drones can go into
places that people can't go.

00:09:04.180 --> 00:09:07.100
Like to search and rescue
and to earthquake areas.

00:09:07.100 --> 00:09:10.040
They're also used
for medical purposes.

00:09:10.040 --> 00:09:14.340
So, science and science
fiction isn't that far apart.

00:09:14.340 --> 00:09:17.670
So, one of the key elements

00:09:17.670 --> 00:09:21.410
of Explorer Academy is
Cruz's mother was working

00:09:21.410 --> 00:09:24.650
on a secret formula
when she was killed

00:09:24.650 --> 00:09:27.340
in a mysterious lab accident.

00:09:27.340 --> 00:09:33.140
And I decided to use what
I knew about snake venom

00:09:33.140 --> 00:09:35.680
and scorpion venom
and animal venoms

00:09:35.680 --> 00:09:37.900
in general as a key plot point.

00:09:37.900 --> 00:09:41.480
Because we're using those for
medicinal purposes in science.

00:09:41.480 --> 00:09:44.170
And one of the explorers
that helped me with that,

00:09:44.170 --> 00:09:45.950
his name is Zoltan Takacs.

00:09:45.950 --> 00:09:47.790
